          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2017-05-23T13:20:46Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Volunteer Income Tax Assistance Permanence Act of 2017</b></p> <p>This bill directs the Internal Revenue Service (IRS) to establish a Community Volunteer Income Tax Assistance Matching Grant Program to provide matching funds for the development, expansion, or continuation of tax preparation programs to assist low-income taxpayers and members of underserved populations. </p> <p>The program must be substantially similar to the Community Volunteer Income Tax Assistance matching grants demonstration program established under the Consolidated Appropriations Act, 2008. </p> <p>Unless otherwise provided by a specific appropriation, the IRS may not allocate more than $30 million per fiscal year (exclusive of costs of administering the program) for the program. </p>]]></text>
